The paper proposes a novel approach for modeling temporal heterogeneous graph data for community detection task. The approach involves using graph convolutional networks (GCN) to embed spatial and node attribute information, and temporal convolutional networks (TCN) to capture long-term evolutionary patterns. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.SOC (Computational Social Science), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). However, given the focus on community detection task and the use of GCN and TCN, cs.LG and cs.SI are the most likely sub-categories.
